text: I want to express my sincere thanks to @Jerrybadershow for his years of service to conservative ideas on the Northeast WI airwaves. He has ALWAYS argued for what he believes in with respect, honesty, and civility – something we could all use more, not less of in our daily lives.

Today, we heard Sec. Mattis' starkest warning yet about the dangers of failing to fund our military. After the House once again passed full-year defense spending, it is up to my colleagues in the Senate to act decisively to give our troops the resources they need.

Sec. Mattis @HASCRepublicans hearing: servicemembers "are putting themselves in harm’s way, in effect signing a blank check payable to the American people with their lives. They do so despite Congress’ abrogation of its Constitutional responsibility to provide stable funding."
Happy Birthday to @SpeakerRyan. He has more than a decade on me and 3 kids... but somehow has more hair and a higher approval rating among members of my family than I do.
Two days ago in the House, we did our part to keep the U.S. government open, and work toward an agreement that will get us out from under budgetary dysfunction.

Last night we voted to fund the gov't for just 28 days. Whether or not the Senate votes to shut it down, it's irresponsible for Congress to go home for 9 of them. We should stay here and get our work done for the American people.

Lock us in the Capitol until we do.
